commit.message:
Rename sh.args() to sh._args() interally

Our custom importer lets it still be imported as sh.args.

This is to avoid breaking the def foo(*args, **kwargs) convention that would rewrite args() from outer scope.
adding missing python2.6 helper methods
reverting set literals, which do not exist in python2.6
Add whitespace changes from pycharm's autoformatter
Fix warnings from pycharm
Include test.py in flake8 check
Fix test suite for my symlinked homedir
Fix for function that was renamed
Enable flake8 testing on sh.py. Set max linelength to 120
Fix flake8 warnings. Ignore warnings on lambdas and bare excepts.
Fix logic error from previous commit
Remove more trailing whitespace
Use more precise assert methods
Clean up trailing whitespace

Revert "Use id() for equality between running commands"

This reverts commit 9ab76ec6065277dfef11d06398ff440c63330443.

Use id() for equality between running commands

Use id() instead of the expensive unicode() that has the side effect of actually running the command if it is not already running, an blocking until the command has finished running.
